Author: Ben Frederickson <github@benfrederickson.com>
Date:   Tue Feb 20 09:38:37 2018 -0800

    Normalize 2-way subset relationships.

    With 2 sets, when one is a subset of the other - the diagrams generated could sometimes
    place both circles at the same coordinates. While this is correct for minimizing the loss
    function it doesn't look ideal (https://github.com/benfred/venn.js/issues/120)

    We already had some code to normalize venn diagrams to make them look consistent (axis
    align major sets, rearrange disjoint componenets, mirror image if needed etc). As a fix
    during normalization, I'm detecting if one of the disjoint components is a subset and
    moving the smaller circle off to one side.
