commit 14a4acb2301f00ebae9b1af00da9e0983e2c4512
Author: Ben Frederickson <ben@zite.com>
Date:   Mon Jan 26 22:37:31 2015 -0800

    New API

    I wanted to be able to add labels to the intersection areas, which requires
    some breaking changes to the API for drawing venn diagrams. Since this would
    have broken backwards compatibility anyways, I thought I'd make some cleanups
    at the same time.

    Changes are:

        * Use the standard d3 style for reusable charts: http://bost.ocks.org/mike/chart/
        * Allow labels on intersection areas (see examples/venn_venn.html)
        * Set ids don't have to be dense integers, can be arbitrary strings that are also used for the labels
        * Transitions on new/old sets are handled appropiately (see https://github.com/benfred/venn.js/issues/32)

    Still a work in progress
